The overall pattern here is that multiple legitimate-sounding processes (chrome, Calculator) and powershell are performing registry writes, process access, and loading system files. While each event on its own isn't necessarily suspicious, the combination—especially the repeated registry changes by chrome.exe and powershell—could indicate malicious activity trying to stay persistent or inject code.

I'm leaning towards this batch being interesting because of the frequency and types of events involving these processes, especially the use of powershell.exe which is commonly used in attacks. The confidence isn't super high, maybe around 0.6, since some of the events could be normal user activity.
